WEBVTT

00:12.403 --> 00:14.753
- They call it"a bank robbery gone wrong,"

00:14.797 --> 00:16.581
except we did everything right.

00:16.625 --> 00:20.585
Us getting picked upwas just--whatever, dumb luck.

00:20.629 --> 00:23.545
- Is that what you call it,
old-timer, dumb luck?

00:23.588 --> 00:25.242
- Mostly just dumb.

00:25.286 --> 00:27.505
- [sighs]
- [chuckles]

00:27.549 --> 00:29.899
- It's just messed up,you know?

00:29.942 --> 00:32.902
People are gonna look backat this thing me and my dad did

00:32.945 --> 00:35.513
and not remember itfor what it was...

00:35.557 --> 00:37.298
the perfect crime.

00:37.341 --> 00:40.649
♪

00:40.692 --> 00:43.260
- Pop?
Pop, you all right?

00:43.304 --> 00:44.653
My dad's not breathing!

00:44.696 --> 00:46.263
[knocks loudly]
- Hey, old-timer.

00:46.307 --> 00:47.830
- Stop the van!
- Hey!

00:47.873 --> 00:49.832
♪

00:49.875 --> 00:51.834
Hey, can you hear me?
Pop?

00:51.877 --> 00:54.358
♪

00:54.402 --> 00:57.318
- Stay back, okay?

00:57.361 --> 00:58.884
♪

00:58.928 --> 01:00.843
Hey, you okay?

01:00.886 --> 01:02.323
- What are yougonna do to him?

01:02.366 --> 01:04.455
- All right, relax.
- And what are you gonna do--

01:04.499 --> 01:10.505
♪

01:12.507 --> 01:13.551
Dad!

01:13.595 --> 01:16.554
- [gasping]

01:16.598 --> 01:22.517
♪

01:22.560 --> 01:24.780
- You coming?
- I'm out.

01:24.823 --> 01:31.656
♪

01:31.700 --> 01:33.354
- Wrap it up, Stevie.

01:33.397 --> 01:35.878
♪

01:35.921 --> 01:38.533
- [groans]

01:38.576 --> 01:41.188
- What do you want to do
with these guys?

01:41.231 --> 01:48.238
♪

01:51.807 --> 01:54.810
[indistinct chatter]

01:57.465 --> 02:00.729
- [breathes deeply,clears throat]

02:03.253 --> 02:05.386
- I'm sorry.
Are you waiting to order?

02:05.429 --> 02:07.910
- No, no, no, sorry.Already did. It's all yours.

02:11.609 --> 02:13.220
- I got myself in a rut--

02:13.263 --> 02:16.571
found the crab dumplings
and refuse to stray.

02:16.614 --> 02:18.225
What would you do
to shake things up?

02:18.268 --> 02:19.574
[pop music playing quietly]

02:19.617 --> 02:23.230
- It depends.How do you feel about spice?

02:23.273 --> 02:25.014
- I don't mind a little heat.

02:26.058 --> 02:27.973
- Hey, Dad.

02:28.017 --> 02:29.801
- Looking at the fish.

02:29.845 --> 02:31.934
- He keeps telling methat the young one's sick.

02:31.977 --> 02:33.588
I think he's just sleeping.

02:33.631 --> 02:35.807
- Hmm.
- LaCroix?

02:35.851 --> 02:38.593
- Yeah.
Thanks.

02:38.636 --> 02:40.247
Bon appétit.

02:40.290 --> 02:43.250
[tender music]

02:43.293 --> 02:45.556
♪

02:45.600 --> 02:47.645
- She liked you.
- Who?

02:47.689 --> 02:48.951
- The blonde lady.

02:48.994 --> 02:50.953
I think she was gonna
ask you out on a date.

02:50.996 --> 02:53.564
- I don't think so.
- [chuckles]

02:53.608 --> 02:55.262
Did you want her to?

02:55.305 --> 02:57.481
[cell phone rings]

02:57.525 --> 02:59.440
- LaCroix.

02:59.483 --> 03:02.269
- Our newest poster boys
are the father-and-son team

03:02.312 --> 03:03.748
of Blake and Steven Wilson.

03:03.792 --> 03:05.620
They were on their way
from Minnesota to Connecticut

03:05.663 --> 03:08.275
to face charges
for a bank heist in New Haven.

03:08.318 --> 03:11.669
They overpowered the guards and
left them for dead in a van,

03:11.713 --> 03:14.672
which was found next to an
abandoned barn in Woodbridge,

03:14.716 --> 03:16.935
shot point-blank
with their GLOCK 19s.

03:16.979 --> 03:19.808
- We have footage
on the New Haven bank job.

03:19.851 --> 03:23.768
- The skinny one with the .45,
that's sonny boy Steven.

03:23.812 --> 03:25.727
The rifleman
with the linebacker build,

03:25.770 --> 03:27.032
that's Blake.

03:27.076 --> 03:28.295
He's been in and out of prison
his whole life

03:28.338 --> 03:29.513
for bank robbery.

03:29.557 --> 03:31.036
He just completed
a 12-year stint last year.

03:31.080 --> 03:33.952
- Wasted no time
getting back in the saddle.

03:33.996 --> 03:34.997
Steven's story?

03:35.040 --> 03:36.564
- Kid's 18--no record.

03:36.607 --> 03:38.479
- Until Daddy
came back into his life.

03:38.522 --> 03:40.132
What's that
on the security guard?

03:40.176 --> 03:42.831
- A bomb vest--that's how they
managed to get into the vault.

03:42.874 --> 03:44.789
They got away with just
under a million in cash.

03:44.833 --> 03:46.400
They were caught
two weeks later

03:46.443 --> 03:48.010
at a fishing resort
in Minnesota.

03:48.053 --> 03:51.318
- Rob a bank, go fishing.Talk about living the life.

03:51.361 --> 03:53.668
- Well, their plan
was to escape across to Canada,

03:53.711 --> 03:55.496
but young Steven
decided to splash out

03:55.539 --> 03:57.367
on a couple of $1,000 escorts.

03:57.411 --> 03:59.413
He got drunk.
The cops were called.

03:59.456 --> 04:01.110
- Blake would've known better--

04:01.153 --> 04:03.330
career criminal,
hardened ex-con.

04:03.373 --> 04:04.853
How were they planning on
crossing into Canada?

04:04.896 --> 04:07.072
- With two
expertly forged passports.

04:07.116 --> 04:09.074
- If Blake's looking to get
out of the country again,

04:09.118 --> 04:12.034
he's gonna need another 50
for new passports--maybe more.

04:12.077 --> 04:14.515
- Won't be long till
they're robbing banks again.

04:14.558 --> 04:16.473
- Let's get
some TECS border stops,

04:16.517 --> 04:18.562
BOLOs, photos to all
ports of entry

04:18.606 --> 04:20.521
on the northern border.
- On it.

04:20.564 --> 04:22.436
- Kid might be looking
to get off the train.

04:22.479 --> 04:25.569
Killing guards--likely
the Dad's handiwork.

04:25.613 --> 04:27.049
Stevie was just a college boy

04:27.092 --> 04:29.878
in it for the money
and the party girls.

04:29.921 --> 04:33.403
Might not have bargained
for this kind of violence.

04:33.447 --> 04:35.579
We have any family
he might reach out to?

04:35.623 --> 04:37.059
- A mother in Bridgeport.

04:37.102 --> 04:39.627
She left Blake 12 years ago
when he was sent away.

04:39.670 --> 04:42.369
[dramatic music]

04:42.412 --> 04:44.109
♪

04:44.153 --> 04:46.416
- This is unbelievable.

04:46.460 --> 04:48.679
His father's got him
mixed up in murder now?

04:48.723 --> 04:50.681
Listen, Stevie
was never in trouble

04:50.725 --> 04:51.682
until Blake
came looking for him

04:51.726 --> 04:53.031
when he got out of prison.

04:53.075 --> 04:54.903
- What was Stevie doing
back then?

04:54.946 --> 04:57.514
- He was trying to get
into Trinity College.

04:57.558 --> 05:00.387
He didn't get into any
of the colleges he applied to,

05:00.430 --> 05:03.085
so backup plan was to take
community college courses

05:03.128 --> 05:04.478
and transfer.

05:04.521 --> 05:07.089
- Doesn't sound like youhad much faith in the plan.

05:07.132 --> 05:11.963
- Stevie's ego is fragile.
We just have to support him.

05:12.007 --> 05:15.053
- We being?
- Oh, me and Wesley, my oldest.

05:15.097 --> 05:16.446
Just finished his PhD

05:16.490 --> 05:19.014
in sustainable energy
from Stanford.

05:19.057 --> 05:22.060
- That's a tough act to follow.
- No one expected him to.

05:22.104 --> 05:25.107
I always told Stevie he's gonna
make his mark another way.

05:25.150 --> 05:28.066
- Stevie was six whenhis father went into prison--

05:28.110 --> 05:31.505
young enough to thinkof his dad as a hero.

05:31.548 --> 05:33.594
Would Blake exploit that?
- He would've.

05:33.637 --> 05:35.813
And I was 17 when we met.

05:35.857 --> 05:37.424
Promised me the world.

05:37.467 --> 05:39.600
Only thing
Blake loves more than stealing

05:39.643 --> 05:42.037
is philandering and fishing.

05:42.080 --> 05:43.995
After a big score,
he'd take off,

05:44.039 --> 05:45.345
wouldn't come back

05:45.388 --> 05:47.085
till he had his fill
of walleye and loose women.

05:47.129 --> 05:49.131
Even in prison--
came to find out

05:49.174 --> 05:51.220
he's got pen pals, women.

05:51.263 --> 05:53.483
I got my boys,
and I never looked back.

05:56.704 --> 06:00.795
Is it too late for Stevie?
- We'll know when we find him.

06:00.838 --> 06:02.666
[cell phone rings]

06:02.710 --> 06:04.973
- Oh, wait.
This is Wesley.

06:05.016 --> 06:06.801
I'm gonna take this.

06:08.193 --> 06:09.934
- Pen pals--

06:09.978 --> 06:13.155
maybe one of them's
helping Blake on the outside.

06:13.198 --> 06:16.158
Steven was in a vulnerable
place in his life--

06:16.201 --> 06:19.074
rejected by colleges,
a half-ass plan.

06:19.117 --> 06:21.076
He would've been ripe
for the picking by his old man.

06:21.119 --> 06:23.992
- Hey, boss, tracked down all
of Blake's known associates--

06:24.035 --> 06:27.952
All dead ends, literally.
Blake's the last man standing.

06:27.996 --> 06:30.999
- I asked New Haven's DOCabout Blake's pen pals.

06:31.042 --> 06:32.522
There's one he's kepton the string

06:32.566 --> 06:35.830
for the last three years--she calls herself his fiancée.

06:35.873 --> 06:38.528
Prison is sending us scans
of their correspondence.

06:38.572 --> 06:41.488
- Ah, this I got to see.
[keys clacking]

06:41.531 --> 06:42.837
- Her name is Jeri Eaton--

06:42.880 --> 06:45.709
28, lives in Cranston,Rhode Island.

06:45.753 --> 06:48.843
- "I experience with you
a miraculous spiritual unity,

06:48.886 --> 06:50.975
a co-mingling of inner lives."

06:51.019 --> 06:53.500
- "Spiritual unity," fancy way
of saying

06:53.543 --> 06:55.023
aiding and abetting
a fugitive.

06:55.066 --> 06:59.070
♪

06:59.114 --> 07:01.290
- You see
a free outlet anywhere?

07:01.333 --> 07:04.511
♪

07:04.554 --> 07:05.903
- Here, let me help you
with that.

07:05.947 --> 07:08.515
♪

07:08.558 --> 07:09.820
[cell phone thuds]

07:09.864 --> 07:13.084
♪

07:13.128 --> 07:16.740
Why don't you shoot up a flare
while you're at it?

07:16.784 --> 07:19.003
- [chuckles]Right, should've known better.

07:19.047 --> 07:20.744
♪

07:20.788 --> 07:22.529
- Yeah, well, that makes
two of us.

07:22.572 --> 07:24.226
- About time.
- Sorry about that.

07:24.269 --> 07:26.228
- Maybe I shouldn't
have brought him along.

07:26.271 --> 07:28.665
- He just wantsto please you, Blake.

07:28.709 --> 07:31.059
It's nice, isn't it?
- Hey, excuse me!

07:31.102 --> 07:33.888
- Case in point--I say,
"Keep a low profile."

07:33.931 --> 07:35.846
And what does that nimrod do?
- Hello? Hey!

07:35.890 --> 07:38.153
- Look, you deal with him.
I'll be in the car.

07:38.196 --> 07:41.243
- Excuse me.
You forgot my nuggets.

07:41.286 --> 07:43.898
Hello?
My nuggets?

07:43.941 --> 07:46.857
Hello?
- Time to go.

07:46.901 --> 07:48.729
- They forgot
his corn dog nuggets.

07:48.772 --> 07:50.600
He's already pissed off at me
enough as it is.

07:50.644 --> 07:53.777
- There's plenty of foodwhere we're going--don't worry.

07:53.821 --> 07:55.605
What?

07:55.649 --> 07:57.564
- Nothing, it's just...

07:57.607 --> 08:00.262
♪

08:00.305 --> 08:01.959
I'm glad you're here.

08:02.003 --> 08:05.093
I think you're really good
for him--for both of us.

08:05.136 --> 08:06.964
♪

08:07.008 --> 08:08.357
- Come on.

08:08.400 --> 08:10.925
♪

08:10.968 --> 08:13.580
- Jeri's a true-crime fangirl--

08:13.623 --> 08:16.147
Scott Peterson,Jeffrey MacDonald,

08:16.191 --> 08:17.366
Kenneth Bianchi.

08:17.409 --> 08:18.889
- She has a flair
for the dramatic.

08:18.933 --> 08:20.848
- Blake wasn't
her only prison pen pal.

08:20.891 --> 08:22.327
Over the past five years,

08:22.371 --> 08:24.765
she's written letters
to six other convicts.

08:24.808 --> 08:25.983
- Jeri, you minx.

08:26.027 --> 08:27.811
- But she's been Blake's
exclusive pen pal

08:27.855 --> 08:29.117
for the past year.

08:29.160 --> 08:31.206
- Super says
he hasn't seen Jeri in a week.

08:31.249 --> 08:32.599
She's a good tenant,

08:32.642 --> 08:35.863
pays her rent
on time and in cash.

08:35.906 --> 08:38.343
Nice catch.

08:38.387 --> 08:40.911
Walleye, good 15-pounder.

08:40.955 --> 08:42.609
I'd be cheesing, too.

08:42.652 --> 08:44.785
- Crook with a heart of gold.

08:44.828 --> 08:47.135
She and Blake must have had
a little honeymoon

08:47.178 --> 08:48.832
before the New Haven bank job.

08:48.876 --> 08:50.181
They even took junior along.

08:50.225 --> 08:52.619
- Maybe the next honeymoon'sin Canada.

08:52.662 --> 08:54.229
- They'll need money for that.

08:54.272 --> 08:56.927
You said she paid
for her rent in cash?

08:56.971 --> 08:59.147
They're gonna have to findthat cash somewhere.

08:59.190 --> 09:00.801
- There's this.

09:00.844 --> 09:03.760
"Here's a shot of you and Bill
I thought you'd enjoy.

09:03.804 --> 09:05.327
"By the way,
these are the November dates

09:05.370 --> 09:07.677
"I need bartenders for.

09:07.721 --> 09:11.246
I can do 500 cash each
if you commit to all."

09:11.289 --> 09:14.162
Letterhead says
"Marley York Catering."

09:14.205 --> 09:17.339
- [sighs] Caterer with a bunch
of cash on hand.

09:17.382 --> 09:20.995
♪

09:21.038 --> 09:23.432
- Got one bullet
to the shoulder,

09:23.475 --> 09:25.826
another to the back
of the head.

09:25.869 --> 09:28.045
- Multiple gunshot wounds
across the back,

09:28.089 --> 09:29.394
both shot from behind

09:29.438 --> 09:31.701
probably while making
a play for the door.

09:31.745 --> 09:34.791
- There's blood around
her lips, no visible wound.

09:34.835 --> 09:38.055
Maybe she bit one of 'em.
- Good for her.

09:38.099 --> 09:40.231
Hopefully she gave
one of them tetanus.

09:40.275 --> 09:46.455
♪

09:46.498 --> 09:48.457
- Looks like
they found the cash.

09:48.500 --> 09:51.242
- And Chef York's wardrobe.

09:51.286 --> 09:52.417
- Oh, my God.

09:52.461 --> 09:55.029
- Jeri helped herself
to a few dresses.

09:55.072 --> 09:58.249
- They snagged a few bottles
of champagne on the way out.

09:58.293 --> 10:00.382
Blood on the box could be
the same person

10:00.425 --> 10:01.905
that got bit by the chef.

10:01.949 --> 10:04.299
- Blake is losing his grip...

10:04.342 --> 10:06.083
killing anybody
that gets in his way.

10:06.127 --> 10:07.781
- If Stevie thought
life with his dad

10:07.824 --> 10:09.870
was all fun and games,
he's having his eyes opened.

10:09.913 --> 10:13.482
- He'll make excuses
for his dad. I did.

10:13.525 --> 10:16.920
First time my dad took me
to the Saratoga Racetrack,

10:16.964 --> 10:18.705
I was 14.

10:18.748 --> 10:20.924
By the fourth race,
he was completely broke.

10:20.968 --> 10:24.058
I had 20 bucks in my pocket
from my paper route.

10:24.101 --> 10:27.844
That went, but on the way home,
I felt good about things.

10:27.888 --> 10:29.890
I told myself,
"My dad just showed me

10:29.933 --> 10:33.850
how important I was to him
by borrowing money from me."

10:33.894 --> 10:35.373
♪

10:35.417 --> 10:36.853
- We found Chef York's
cell phone

10:36.897 --> 10:38.115
on the floor of the closet.

10:38.159 --> 10:40.465
- Last outgoing callwas at 9:16 this morning

10:40.509 --> 10:43.468
to a Boon Pharmacyin Cranston, Rhode Island.

10:43.512 --> 10:45.166
- Jeri's home turf.

10:45.209 --> 10:48.996
♪

10:49.039 --> 10:51.433
- Isn't this lace numbera miracle worker?

10:51.476 --> 10:53.478
- You look great
in anything you wear.

10:53.522 --> 10:55.176
Isn't that right, Dad?

10:55.219 --> 11:02.226
♪

11:06.013 --> 11:08.189
- How's the hand?
- It's cool.

11:08.232 --> 11:11.235
It's just a bite.
I can take it.

11:11.279 --> 11:13.977
- You always were a tough kid.

11:14.021 --> 11:20.897
♪

11:20.941 --> 11:23.552
Look, Stevie, uh...

11:23.595 --> 11:24.988
I know it was hard,

11:25.032 --> 11:27.512
my not being aroundwhen you were growing up,

11:27.556 --> 11:30.167
but I appreciate

11:30.211 --> 11:33.040
the chance to make up for it.

11:33.083 --> 11:36.043
[tender music]

11:36.086 --> 11:38.306
♪

11:38.349 --> 11:40.525
- [voice breaking]Thank you, Dad.

11:40.569 --> 11:47.576
♪

11:50.535 --> 11:52.929
- Hey, how about wego down to the dock

11:52.973 --> 11:54.931
while there's stillsome daylight?

11:54.975 --> 11:56.803
- Yeah, sure.

11:56.846 --> 11:58.500
[knock at door]

11:58.543 --> 12:01.155
- No.
[guns cock]

12:01.198 --> 12:03.940
Don't.
I know who it is.

12:03.984 --> 12:05.246
- You what?

12:05.289 --> 12:07.814
- It's a friend I called
from the chef's phone,

12:07.857 --> 12:09.467
which I totally left behind.

12:09.511 --> 12:11.469
I learn my lessons, babe.

12:11.513 --> 12:14.472
[tense music]

12:14.516 --> 12:16.518
♪

12:16.561 --> 12:19.913
- If this friend of yoursisn't right...

12:19.956 --> 12:21.349
they're dead.

12:21.392 --> 12:25.570
♪

12:30.184 --> 12:32.055
- We'll need plate readers
on all routes

12:32.099 --> 12:33.448
in and out of Providence.

12:33.491 --> 12:36.277
Wilson's smart enough
to stay off the interstates.

12:36.320 --> 12:37.800
- Okay, so let's focuson Routes 6...

12:37.844 --> 12:38.932
[cell phone rings]

12:38.975 --> 12:41.369
44, and 146.

12:41.412 --> 12:42.805
- What you got?

12:42.849 --> 12:45.373
- Yeah, Bethany Hogan,
works in the pharmacy.

12:45.416 --> 12:47.810
She went home sick
three hours ago.

12:47.854 --> 12:50.073
Took a first-aid kit
and some pain meds with her.

12:50.117 --> 12:52.206
- Got ya.
Let's go.

12:56.079 --> 12:58.299
- [chuckles]

12:58.342 --> 13:00.867
You really shouldtake it easy with that.

13:00.910 --> 13:03.826
- Where's my manners?
You want some?

13:03.870 --> 13:07.830
- Okay, but not too much.[chuckles]

13:07.874 --> 13:10.702
Jeri said you were sweet.She was right.

13:10.746 --> 13:13.705
[ominous music]

13:13.749 --> 13:16.143
♪

13:16.186 --> 13:17.971
- Can you grab us another one?

13:18.014 --> 13:21.365
I'm almost out,and your dad's gone flat.

13:21.409 --> 13:23.193
- You're not almost done.
You're done.

13:23.237 --> 13:25.674
- Wha--I'm just tryingto loosen you up.

13:25.717 --> 13:27.981
- Yeah, by bringing
some stranger in here?

13:28.024 --> 13:29.460
- Look, if you're worriedabout me,

13:29.504 --> 13:32.028
I swear, my lips are sealed.
- No one's talking to you.

13:32.072 --> 13:33.682
- Babe, why can't we just havea nice time?

13:33.725 --> 13:35.162
I tried so hardto make everything good.

13:35.205 --> 13:36.772
- Jeri, I swear--

13:36.816 --> 13:37.947
- And, hey, for the record,one of those bottles

13:37.991 --> 13:40.994
would run you,like, $200 in a restaurant.

13:41.037 --> 13:42.952
- Oh.

13:42.996 --> 13:44.780
♪

13:44.824 --> 13:48.958
Oh, well that
changes everything.

13:49.002 --> 13:50.177
- [screams]

13:50.220 --> 13:53.180
- Here!
Yeah, knock yourself out!

13:53.223 --> 13:55.182
[glass shatters]

13:55.225 --> 14:00.013
♪

14:00.056 --> 14:01.841
- Don't look at me.

14:01.884 --> 14:03.843
♪

14:03.886 --> 14:06.236
- I can't believe what thatson of a bitch just did to her.

14:06.280 --> 14:07.803
- Easy, that's my dad
you're talking about.

14:07.847 --> 14:09.413
- Do you know how muchshe loves him?

14:09.457 --> 14:10.980
She doesn't deserve that.

14:11.024 --> 14:13.896
♪

14:13.940 --> 14:16.725
- Roughly same age,
same education.

14:16.768 --> 14:20.468
Two years at UMass for Bethany,
two at Tufts for Jeri.

14:20.511 --> 14:23.166
But their paths do cross
on Facebook Messenger

14:23.210 --> 14:25.212
where they dish
about their shared passion,

14:25.255 --> 14:28.432
Love on the Inside,
an online community

14:28.476 --> 14:30.086
who date the incarcerated.

14:30.130 --> 14:34.743
- All right, dating a convict.I don't get it.

14:34.786 --> 14:36.919
- You always know
where your man is,

14:36.963 --> 14:39.226
that he's not up to something
with your BFF.

14:39.269 --> 14:41.793
- Amen to that.
- It's safe.

14:41.837 --> 14:44.274
No physical contact,
no intimacy.

14:44.318 --> 14:46.929
You think you matter
in that convict's life.

14:46.973 --> 14:49.236
- Like a sheep mattersto a wolf.

14:49.279 --> 14:50.846
Convicts have written textbooks

14:50.890 --> 14:52.804
on how to workyour prison bride.

14:52.848 --> 14:55.285
- So Bethany got invited
to keep Stevie company

14:55.329 --> 14:57.200
while Dad and Jeri
do their thing.

14:57.244 --> 14:59.507
- They got girls.
They got champagne.

14:59.550 --> 15:02.423
All Blake needs now
is a place to cast a line.

15:02.466 --> 15:05.861
- Last ping on Bethany's GPSis 20 miles east of Providence.

15:05.905 --> 15:07.950
It's right overthe Massachusetts state line.

15:07.994 --> 15:11.519
- Long Pond Lake's nearby.
It's known for its walleye.

15:13.303 --> 15:16.132
- Fishing camps, lake resorts.

15:16.176 --> 15:18.091
- On it.

15:18.134 --> 15:20.876
[keys clacking]

15:20.920 --> 15:22.878
- [breathing heavily]

15:22.922 --> 15:26.273
[suspenseful music]

15:26.316 --> 15:27.274
- Flashing.

15:27.317 --> 15:29.232
♪

15:29.276 --> 15:30.451
- [grunts]
- Go, go.

15:30.494 --> 15:35.108
♪

15:35.151 --> 15:37.545
- Still warm.
Didn't miss him by much.

15:37.588 --> 15:43.420
♪

15:43.464 --> 15:46.467
- This is Agent Crosby.
You did?

15:46.510 --> 15:49.426
Okay. Where at?

15:49.470 --> 15:52.081
[dramatic music]

15:52.125 --> 15:55.258
Yeah, all right.Thanks.

15:55.302 --> 15:57.478
They found Bethany's Priusabout a quarter mile

15:57.521 --> 15:59.132
down the roadhidden in the woods.

15:59.175 --> 16:01.482
- They must have taken off
in Jeri's car.

16:01.525 --> 16:04.485
- The ice on the lake--
it's broken up near the dock.

16:04.528 --> 16:08.489
♪

16:08.532 --> 16:10.012
We got a body.

16:10.056 --> 16:17.063
♪

16:30.380 --> 16:32.034
Bethany Hogan.

16:32.078 --> 16:34.384
- We got a DB
in the water by the dock.

16:34.428 --> 16:38.040
♪

16:38.084 --> 16:41.174
- Used anchors down there.

16:41.217 --> 16:43.393
Probably from those boats
over there.

16:43.437 --> 16:46.396
Tied it around her
so she wouldn't float up.

16:46.440 --> 16:49.312
- Somebody didn't want
her found anytime soon.

16:49.356 --> 16:51.314
- That was the intention.

16:51.358 --> 16:54.491
The rope slipped,
was poorly tied like this one.

16:54.535 --> 16:56.102
♪

16:56.145 --> 16:58.104
A life-long fisherman
like Blake

16:58.147 --> 17:00.367
would never have made
this kind of mistake, would he?

17:00.410 --> 17:02.195
- No, he wouldn't.

17:02.238 --> 17:04.110
- He wouldn't let anybody else
make it either.

17:04.153 --> 17:05.459
- Nope.

17:05.502 --> 17:09.071
♪

17:09.115 --> 17:11.943
This wasn't Blake's play.

17:11.987 --> 17:15.121
- So what are we saying?

17:15.164 --> 17:17.210
- What I'm saying
is it was Stevie.

17:17.253 --> 17:19.429
He killed her.

17:19.473 --> 17:23.042
I've been looking
at this all wrong.

17:23.085 --> 17:24.086
Damn it.

17:24.130 --> 17:27.611
♪

17:32.573 --> 17:35.576
- ME's preliminary on Bethany--
blunt-force trauma

17:35.619 --> 17:38.535
to the back of the head,
then drowning.

17:43.366 --> 17:45.194
- What's going on, bro?

17:45.238 --> 17:46.717
- [inhales deeply]

17:46.761 --> 17:49.503
I let my own history
muddy my judgment.

17:49.546 --> 17:51.287
It's all right here.

17:51.331 --> 17:53.550
Two security guards in the van,
both shot point-blank.

17:53.594 --> 17:55.552
The whole point of firing at
close range is a direct shot.

17:55.596 --> 17:57.250
These shots were
off the mark, indecisive.

17:57.293 --> 17:58.512
The shooter hesitated.

17:58.555 --> 18:00.340
Whoever grabbed York
didn't have the muscle

18:00.383 --> 18:01.558
or the experience
to control her.

18:01.602 --> 18:03.212
They started shooting.

18:03.256 --> 18:05.040
Ballistics found slugs all over
the back wall of the kitchen,

18:05.084 --> 18:06.694
all from the same gun.

18:06.737 --> 18:08.348
- Panic fire.

18:08.391 --> 18:11.133
- This isn't the work
of a hardened criminal.

18:11.177 --> 18:14.136
This is Stevie making a mess.

18:14.180 --> 18:15.529
He killed all these people

18:15.572 --> 18:17.748
in plain sight
of his dad and Jeri.

18:17.792 --> 18:21.361
Bethany--
he strangled her,

18:21.404 --> 18:23.232
drowned her quietly,

18:23.276 --> 18:25.104
hid her body
at the bottom of the lake,

18:25.147 --> 18:27.367
and then dumped her car
far from the cabin.

18:27.410 --> 18:28.803
- He didn't want Blake and Jeri
to know.

18:28.846 --> 18:30.544
- That's what I'm thinking.

18:30.587 --> 18:33.547
It suggests that Blake
is not too happy

18:33.590 --> 18:36.071
with Stevie's killing spree.

18:36.115 --> 18:38.204
Perhaps there is tension
between the two of them,

18:38.247 --> 18:40.119
maybe something we can exploit.

18:40.162 --> 18:41.729
- Okay, let's dig into that.

18:41.772 --> 18:44.732
[dramatic music]

18:44.775 --> 18:47.213
♪

18:47.256 --> 18:49.302
- We don't need
to worry about Bethany.

18:49.345 --> 18:50.520
She's just not the type to--

18:50.564 --> 18:53.436
- Sneak out in the middleof the night?

18:53.480 --> 18:55.743
We're fightingfor our lives, Jeri.

18:55.786 --> 18:58.485
That's the cornerthat kid pushed us into.

18:58.528 --> 18:59.486
- I know.

18:59.529 --> 19:00.791
He's got me worried, too,

19:00.835 --> 19:03.577
but the kid
worships you, Blake.

19:03.620 --> 19:08.103
- Yeah, he's a live wire,and he's in the way.

19:08.147 --> 19:14.153
♪

19:14.196 --> 19:16.590
- It's a cakewalk,
just like you said.

19:16.633 --> 19:20.637
It's all there--
no guards, back exit.

19:20.681 --> 19:22.465
So?

19:22.509 --> 19:24.250
- See you on the other side.

19:24.293 --> 19:31.126
♪

19:31.170 --> 19:33.346
- Everyone stays on the ground!

19:33.389 --> 19:35.304
No one talks!

19:35.348 --> 19:39.265
No one moves,
and no one dies!

19:39.308 --> 19:40.875
I said don't move!
- I'm not!

19:40.918 --> 19:42.224
- Not now!

19:42.268 --> 19:43.486
You were just a second ago
right over here!

19:43.530 --> 19:45.314
- I don't know
what you're talking about.

19:45.358 --> 19:46.359
- Don't!

19:46.402 --> 19:48.230
♪

19:48.274 --> 19:51.146
- The alarm, bitch!
- Let it go!

19:51.190 --> 19:53.148
- Is that what you
were stupid enough to do?

19:53.192 --> 19:54.454
- Leave her alone.

19:54.497 --> 19:58.458
♪

19:58.501 --> 20:01.243
[whimpering]
[gun cocks]

20:01.287 --> 20:04.290
[people screaming]

20:05.465 --> 20:07.380
- what the hell are you doing?

20:07.423 --> 20:09.382
♪

20:09.425 --> 20:12.428
- [screaming]

20:13.777 --> 20:15.910
- The big one
emptied the drawer so fast.

20:15.953 --> 20:18.347
I thought
maybe he took the bait money.

20:18.391 --> 20:19.783
He grabbed everything but.

20:19.827 --> 20:21.524
- Is therea back exit downstairs?

20:21.568 --> 20:22.873
- Not an official one.

20:22.917 --> 20:24.832
There's a way out
through the service corridor.

20:24.875 --> 20:27.269
- You remember anything else
about the two men?

20:27.313 --> 20:29.184
- The big one wanted to go,

20:29.228 --> 20:30.794
but the skinny one
wouldn't listen.

20:30.838 --> 20:34.668
After he shot Ryan,
the big one dragged him out.

20:34.711 --> 20:37.540
- Physically?
- Pulled him by the collar.

20:37.584 --> 20:40.543
The big one was pissed.

20:40.587 --> 20:43.503
- That's it for now.
Thank you.

20:43.546 --> 20:46.419
- Bank manager puts the take
at around 11 grand.

20:46.462 --> 20:49.204
That's 30 grand shy of what
they need for those passports.

20:49.248 --> 20:50.858
- If the Wilson'smake it that far,

20:50.901 --> 20:52.599
the family tiesare looking thin.

20:52.642 --> 20:54.209
- Even with his son's antics,

20:54.253 --> 20:55.906
Blake is proving himself
a total pro,

20:55.950 --> 20:58.213
avoiding the bait money,
knowing about the exit.

20:58.257 --> 21:00.520
- Jeri was probably parked
there in the getaway car.

21:00.563 --> 21:02.870
- Any video with a sight line
to the back exit?

21:02.913 --> 21:03.914
- Got it right here.

21:03.958 --> 21:05.916
- Excellent.
Let's get a look at her.

21:08.354 --> 21:10.225
- Now, I crosscheckedthe timecode.

21:10.269 --> 21:11.835
You got Jeri starting to leave

21:11.879 --> 21:14.577
at the same timethat Stevie shot the employee,

21:14.621 --> 21:17.537
so I'm guessing Jeriheard the shot and panicked.

21:17.580 --> 21:19.887
- She was gonna run,
but then changed her mind.

21:19.930 --> 21:22.237
- But her impulse was to run.

21:22.281 --> 21:23.717
- She had enough
of the gangster life.

21:23.760 --> 21:25.327
- Maybe we can get her
to run again.

21:25.371 --> 21:26.850
The website she
and Bethany were on--

21:26.894 --> 21:28.330
- Love on the Inside.

21:28.374 --> 21:30.550
- Yeah, yeah, does Jeri
still log on to that?

21:30.593 --> 21:32.639
- Uh, last time was yesterday.

21:32.682 --> 21:35.337
She's not posting but reading
about other ladies

21:35.381 --> 21:37.687
and how they're living it up
with their bad boys.

21:37.731 --> 21:39.254
- All right, well,
we're gonna assume

21:39.298 --> 21:40.734
she doesn't know Stevie
killed Bethany

21:40.777 --> 21:42.475
because Bethany's
about to reach out to Jeri

21:42.518 --> 21:45.260
and coax her away from Blake.
- I'm liking this.

21:45.304 --> 21:46.827
- You would.
- [chuckles]

21:46.870 --> 21:48.611
- All right, hard sellthe story

21:48.655 --> 21:51.266
about Blakedriving Bethany away.

21:51.310 --> 21:53.616
- "Hey, Jeri,
sorry I cut out on you,

21:53.660 --> 21:55.923
but I was forced to
by Blake, who"--

21:55.966 --> 21:59.753
- "Forced himself on me."
- "And that's why I took off."

21:59.796 --> 22:02.712
- "Fearing for my life
and yours."

22:02.756 --> 22:04.453
- "I'm ready to go
to the police."

22:04.497 --> 22:06.934
- "But I won't do it
unless I know you're safe."

22:06.977 --> 22:08.805
- "I'm here for you, Jeri."

22:09.980 --> 22:11.634
- "Just name a place to meet."

22:14.811 --> 22:15.812
- Works for me.

22:17.597 --> 22:19.555
- Send it.

22:19.599 --> 22:23.037
[keys clacking]

22:30.000 --> 22:31.611
- It's Tali.

22:31.654 --> 22:33.526
She said they went back
to the Chinese place

22:33.569 --> 22:36.833
but didn't see my girlfriend--
sad face.

22:38.008 --> 22:40.359
She is a funny one.

22:40.402 --> 22:41.969
- She is.

22:42.012 --> 22:45.625
Seriously, bro, you might've
missed an opportunity.

22:45.668 --> 22:47.583
- Ah, I don't think so.

22:47.627 --> 22:48.845
Tali was there.

22:48.889 --> 22:50.412
If I had have responded,

22:50.456 --> 22:52.849
it might've been difficultfor her.

22:52.893 --> 22:54.808
- I don't know about that.

22:54.851 --> 22:57.854
Tali actually might like
to see you out there.

22:57.898 --> 23:00.640
I think my folks
would be okay with it, too.

23:00.683 --> 23:01.989
[chuckles]

23:02.032 --> 23:04.818
- [chuckles]
I wouldn't know where to start.

23:04.861 --> 23:07.995
- Well, there's dating apps,
but everybody wants

23:08.038 --> 23:09.692
a guaranteed outcome.

23:09.736 --> 23:10.780
That ain't living.

23:10.824 --> 23:12.782
- No, it ain't.

23:12.826 --> 23:15.045
So what do you do?

23:15.089 --> 23:19.441
- Tried and true--
be nice, friendly.

23:19.485 --> 23:21.008
Be open.

23:21.051 --> 23:23.445
♪

23:23.489 --> 23:24.664
[computer beeps]

23:24.707 --> 23:26.492
- It's Jeri.

23:26.535 --> 23:29.364
"Bethany, I've thought
seriously about what you said.

23:29.408 --> 23:32.454
I'll meet you tomorrow at 9:00
behind Garden City Plaza."

23:32.498 --> 23:37.416
♪

23:37.459 --> 23:39.505
[door opens]

23:39.548 --> 23:46.555
♪

23:51.125 --> 23:53.736
[tires squealing]

23:53.780 --> 23:55.782
[siren wailing]

23:55.825 --> 23:57.784
[tires screeching]

23:57.827 --> 24:02.049
♪

24:02.092 --> 24:04.573
- Jeri, I'm Agent LaCroix
of the FBI.

24:04.617 --> 24:07.402
I'd like you to come
with us, please.

24:07.446 --> 24:09.448
Oh, she's on the move!

24:09.491 --> 24:10.753
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

24:10.797 --> 24:12.015
- Let me go!
- Hold on. Hold on.

24:12.059 --> 24:14.104
- Where's Bethany?
That bitch lied to me.

24:14.148 --> 24:15.889
Let me go.
- Easy, lady.

24:15.932 --> 24:18.108
We're not trying to hurt you.
- Come take a look!

24:18.152 --> 24:21.155
- We got a tarp, hacksaw,
garbage bags.

24:21.198 --> 24:22.939
- And inthe glove compartment...

24:22.983 --> 24:25.812
Jeri had a going-away partyplanned for Bethany.

24:25.855 --> 24:27.944
♪

24:32.645 --> 24:35.038
- I didn't want to meet
Bethany, but Stevie made me.

24:35.082 --> 24:37.780
He wanted me to kill her
to shut her up.

24:37.824 --> 24:39.565
- Stevie told you to kill her?
- Yes.

24:39.608 --> 24:40.783
I wouldn't havegone through with it,

24:40.827 --> 24:43.307
but I'm scared of Stevie,and so is Blake.

24:43.351 --> 24:45.571
I mean, after seeing himkill four people...

24:47.007 --> 24:49.662
You know?

24:49.705 --> 24:53.535
- Five people.
Stevie already killed Bethany.

24:53.579 --> 24:57.452
[dramatic music]

24:57.496 --> 24:59.323
And you're lying to us.

24:59.367 --> 25:01.543
Nobody sent you
to the Garden City Plaza.

25:01.587 --> 25:04.372
You resented Bethany
for threatening the fantasy

25:04.415 --> 25:06.330
you'd created around Blake.

25:06.374 --> 25:07.767
But then there's Stevie.

25:07.810 --> 25:09.725
- We saw how you almost
drove away when you heard

25:09.769 --> 25:10.900
the shooting in the bank.

25:10.944 --> 25:12.598
You wanted to leave
because of Stevie,

25:12.641 --> 25:14.556
but you couldn't
'cause of Blake.

25:14.600 --> 25:16.340
- Whether you agreed
to the murders or not,

25:16.384 --> 25:17.820
you're an accomplice.

25:17.864 --> 25:21.041
If you cooperate,
maybe we could work

25:21.084 --> 25:22.738
something out
for you and Blake.

25:22.782 --> 25:25.567
- You might even get out
of jail at the same time,

25:25.611 --> 25:27.830
be able to pick up
where you left off.

25:27.874 --> 25:34.881
♪

25:36.970 --> 25:38.885
- Who gave Blake
inside information

25:38.928 --> 25:40.582
on the bank in Rehoboth?

25:40.626 --> 25:43.063
- Uh, this guy in New Haven.

25:43.106 --> 25:46.806
I don't know his name, but wewent to his place just before.

25:46.849 --> 25:48.677
- So you can lead us to him?

25:48.721 --> 25:50.810
- It was at night.Blake was driving.

25:50.853 --> 25:53.464
♪

25:53.508 --> 25:56.772
He said the guyowed him $100,000.

25:56.816 --> 25:58.861
He told me to knockon the door.

25:58.905 --> 26:00.950
It was a blue door.

26:00.994 --> 26:03.474
He answered, and then Blakeand Stevie pushed in.

26:03.518 --> 26:05.955
- Great.
What'd he look like?

26:05.999 --> 26:08.567
- He was black, hefty.

26:08.610 --> 26:11.439
He had a hearing aidon his left side.

26:11.482 --> 26:12.614
Blake sent me back to the car,

26:12.658 --> 26:14.007
and I waitedtill they came back,

26:14.050 --> 26:16.400
and then the next day,they hit the bank.

26:16.444 --> 26:19.447
- And what about the 100,000?

26:19.490 --> 26:21.144
- I don't think they got it.

26:21.188 --> 26:23.843
If they did, theywouldn't need to rob anybody.

26:23.886 --> 26:26.628
- Because they had enough
for the passports?

26:26.672 --> 26:28.587
♪

26:28.630 --> 26:30.719
Blake's heading to Canada, yes?

26:30.763 --> 26:32.155
♪

26:32.199 --> 26:34.897
- It's too late
to hold out on us, Jeri.

26:34.941 --> 26:38.553
♪

26:38.597 --> 26:43.732
- Blake knows these people--the Albanians, he calls them.

26:43.776 --> 26:45.908
We gave them $10,000.

26:45.952 --> 26:48.607
They said we had two daysto come up with the rest.

26:48.650 --> 26:50.652
- [sighs]

26:50.696 --> 26:52.785
How much is the rest?

26:52.828 --> 26:54.613
- 50,000.

26:54.656 --> 26:57.528
♪

26:57.572 --> 26:59.748
- These were foundin Jeri's purse--

26:59.792 --> 27:01.968
photos for the fake passports.

27:02.011 --> 27:03.926
Looks like Stevieis the odd man out.

27:03.970 --> 27:05.711
- Blake's cutting him loose.

27:05.754 --> 27:07.843
- Probably not until he's gotthe money for the passports.

27:07.887 --> 27:10.846
At least one more bank robbery.[sighs]

27:10.890 --> 27:12.935
The bank jobthey got arrested for,

27:12.979 --> 27:14.763
the one in New Haventhree months ago,

27:14.807 --> 27:15.851
netted them what?

27:15.895 --> 27:18.811
- Uh, they cleared
almost a mil.

27:18.854 --> 27:21.770
- And they were caught
with 840 grand.

27:21.814 --> 27:24.468
- And take away the 50k
for the passports.

27:24.512 --> 27:25.818
- Right.

27:25.861 --> 27:27.515
- That still leaves 100 grand
unaccounted for.

27:27.558 --> 27:29.169
- Money they might've paid
to an inside man

27:29.212 --> 27:31.084
for information
on the bank job.

27:32.259 --> 27:34.130
Can you cue up
the New Haven bank job?

27:34.174 --> 27:37.177
- Yeah, give me a sec.
- [clears throat]

27:37.220 --> 27:39.701
[keys clacking]

27:39.745 --> 27:46.752
♪

27:49.102 --> 27:51.104
Blow it up.
Play it back.

27:51.147 --> 27:52.671
- Mm-hmm.
- Real slow.

27:52.714 --> 27:59.678
♪

28:01.157 --> 28:03.682
- He's bleeding...

28:03.725 --> 28:05.727
from a blown eardrum.

28:05.771 --> 28:07.555
That's our man.

28:07.598 --> 28:09.992
♪

28:10.036 --> 28:11.167
- Good.

28:11.211 --> 28:14.127
[suspenseful music]

28:14.170 --> 28:16.520
- FBI, freeze!

28:16.564 --> 28:20.220
♪

28:20.263 --> 28:22.526
- Get up!

28:22.570 --> 28:24.180
- [grunts]

28:24.224 --> 28:27.053
- We'll take that as an
admission of guilt, Mr. Green.

28:27.096 --> 28:29.708
- It's an admission of nothing.Okay, it was a panic attack.

28:29.751 --> 28:31.753
I have PTSS to this daybecause of that bank robbery.

28:31.797 --> 28:32.928
- Come on, Mr. Green,

28:32.972 --> 28:34.451
Blake Wilson's girlfriend
described you.

28:34.495 --> 28:36.889
She described your house.
- What are you talking about?

28:36.932 --> 28:38.673
- After your injury,
Tilling Security gave you

28:38.717 --> 28:40.022
a desk job
at their corporate office.

28:40.066 --> 28:41.154
- Come on, come on.

28:41.197 --> 28:42.633
- You have intel
on dozens of banks.

28:42.677 --> 28:43.722
- I didn't help Blake Wilson.

28:43.765 --> 28:45.593
- Don't make us look
for your cut

28:45.636 --> 28:47.856
from the New Haven job.
- I spent it, all right?

28:47.900 --> 28:50.598
I bought my mom a new condo,
but I didn't help Blake Wilson.

28:50.641 --> 28:53.079
I helped Stevie.

28:53.122 --> 28:54.950
- You helped Stevie rob banks?

28:54.994 --> 28:57.823
- Me and Stevie used to work
at a club up in Hartford.

28:57.866 --> 28:59.781
I did security.
He bused tables.

28:59.825 --> 29:01.957
When I got the job at the bank,
Stevie started telling me

29:02.001 --> 29:04.743
about his pops,
how he was getting out of jail

29:04.786 --> 29:08.572
and how he thought he could
talk him into hitting my bank.

29:08.616 --> 29:10.792
- It was his idea?
He reached out to Blake?

29:10.836 --> 29:13.621
- Yes, all he talked about
was his dad,

29:13.664 --> 29:15.101
how he wanted
to be just like him.

29:15.144 --> 29:17.668
He said it was in
his blood, for God's sake.

29:17.712 --> 29:19.932
Got to admit...

29:19.975 --> 29:21.194
Blake's pretty good.

29:21.237 --> 29:23.109
He came up
with the whole bomb vest thing.

29:23.152 --> 29:25.154
It was pretty slick, right?

29:25.198 --> 29:27.635
- And when Blake found outyou had no money left?

29:27.678 --> 29:30.725
- I thought he'd kill me,
but Stevie stepped up for me,

29:30.769 --> 29:32.640
and that's what saved me.

29:32.683 --> 29:35.730
I just had to give up
some information on some banks.

29:35.774 --> 29:37.340
- How many?

29:38.689 --> 29:39.995
- Three.

29:40.039 --> 29:44.043
♪

29:44.086 --> 29:45.827
- It's been almost 36 hours.

29:45.871 --> 29:47.263
What are the Wilsons
waiting for?

29:47.307 --> 29:48.830
- They should've struck by now.

29:48.874 --> 29:50.701
Maybe Blake figured
we got to Jeri.

29:50.745 --> 29:51.920
It's got him spooked.

29:51.964 --> 29:53.617
- Spooked or not,
they need money to get

29:53.661 --> 29:55.271
out of the country, and they're
running out of time,

29:55.315 --> 29:57.099
not to mention
his trigger-happy son

29:57.143 --> 29:59.841
is probably pushing him
to do something.

29:59.885 --> 30:00.929
Maybe it's a bank we missed.

30:00.973 --> 30:02.670
Maybe it's one
they already scouted.

30:02.713 --> 30:04.019
- When would Blake
have found the time?

30:04.063 --> 30:05.760
He did a bank job as soon
as he got out of jail,

30:05.804 --> 30:07.066
and he's been
on the run ever since.

30:07.109 --> 30:08.632
- Maybe it's Stevie.

30:08.676 --> 30:09.895
He's been wanting to fill
his father's shoes

30:09.938 --> 30:12.201
since way before
Blake got out of prison.

30:12.245 --> 30:13.986
- It was in his blood?

30:18.381 --> 30:20.122
- Maybe he struck out
on his own

30:20.166 --> 30:23.647
while he was in Hartford--
get some work experience.

30:23.691 --> 30:26.912
Can you pull up the--
- Bank robberies in Hartford.

30:26.955 --> 30:30.306
- Yeah, while Stevie
was living there.

30:30.350 --> 30:32.743
- Two--all suspects in custody.

30:32.787 --> 30:34.354
And an attempted robbery

30:34.397 --> 30:36.138
at the Green Mountain
Savings and Loan.

30:36.182 --> 30:38.010
Suspect got away.

30:38.053 --> 30:39.838
[key clacks]

30:39.881 --> 30:42.275
Here he is.
- Could be him.

30:42.318 --> 30:43.885
Looks like he lost his nerve.

30:43.929 --> 30:46.235
- But he would've done
his homework on that bank--

30:46.279 --> 30:49.891
research that'd come in
real handy right about now.

30:49.935 --> 30:53.155
Call Hartford PD.
Get 'em out to that bank ASAP.

30:53.199 --> 30:54.896
And let's get the bird
fired up.

30:54.940 --> 30:56.680
[keys clacking]

30:56.724 --> 30:59.858
[dramatic music]

30:59.901 --> 31:02.861
[sirens approaching]

31:02.904 --> 31:05.341
[tires screeching]

31:05.385 --> 31:08.344
[indistinct shouting]

31:09.868 --> 31:12.305
- Have him lock the door.
- Get up, get up!

31:12.348 --> 31:14.873
Get up now!
Lock the door!

31:14.916 --> 31:16.352
♪

31:16.396 --> 31:17.876
Quickly!
- Okay.

31:17.919 --> 31:19.138
[sirens wailing]

31:19.181 --> 31:21.444
It's locked.

31:21.488 --> 31:23.011
- Get on the ground!

31:23.055 --> 31:30.062
♪

31:37.243 --> 31:38.897
What do we do now?

31:38.940 --> 31:41.029
♪

31:41.073 --> 31:43.336
[indistinct shouting]

31:43.379 --> 31:46.382
♪

31:46.426 --> 31:48.471
- About 30 minutes
into the standoff.

31:48.515 --> 31:50.952
We've made at least two
bad guys through the windows.

31:50.996 --> 31:53.085
Area's secure.
Snipers are in place.

31:53.128 --> 31:55.261
- Gonna join you guys on top.
- Good.

31:55.304 --> 31:57.263
We have a hostage negotiator
on site?

31:57.306 --> 31:59.743
- Lieutenant Thomas,
State Police.

31:59.787 --> 32:01.354
- Agent LaCroix.
Any contact?

32:01.397 --> 32:03.269
- We've been trying--nothing
but silence on the other end.

32:03.312 --> 32:05.271
[gunshot,
distant scream]

32:05.314 --> 32:08.013
- We got shots!
We got shots fired!

32:08.056 --> 32:11.016
[dramatic music]

32:11.059 --> 32:15.237
♪

32:15.281 --> 32:17.805
[cell phone ringing]

32:17.848 --> 32:19.372
- We'll shoot one
every half hour

32:19.415 --> 32:20.764
until our demands are met.

32:20.808 --> 32:22.288
We'll call you back
with a list.

32:22.331 --> 32:25.117
♪

32:25.160 --> 32:26.335
- May I?

32:26.379 --> 32:31.471
♪

32:31.514 --> 32:35.083
[cell phone ringing]

32:35.127 --> 32:37.085
- I said we'd call you back.

32:37.129 --> 32:40.262
- Steven Wilson, this is
Agent LaCroix of the FBI.

32:40.306 --> 32:42.264
I'm taking over
these negotiations.

32:42.308 --> 32:44.049
You need to listen to me
very carefully.

32:44.092 --> 32:45.572
- No, you listen to me.

32:45.615 --> 32:47.226
- You're not dealing
with the State Police anymore.

32:47.269 --> 32:49.010
This is the FBI,
so you're gonna have to put

32:49.054 --> 32:50.316
your big-boy pants on, Stevie.

32:50.359 --> 32:52.796
I will not consider
any of your demands

32:52.840 --> 32:54.494
until you let us remove
that person

32:54.537 --> 32:56.017
from the front of the bank.

32:56.061 --> 32:58.324
This is a serious negotiation
for your lives

32:58.367 --> 33:00.326
and the lives
of your hostages.

33:00.369 --> 33:02.154
I will not let you
turn this into a spectacle.

33:02.197 --> 33:03.851
Are we clear?

33:03.894 --> 33:05.287
♪

33:05.331 --> 33:07.333
- Okay, go ahead.Take the body.

33:07.376 --> 33:09.117
I don't care.

33:09.161 --> 33:12.381
- Good.
- Get him out of there.

33:12.425 --> 33:19.432
♪

33:23.305 --> 33:25.873
- Now, I don't believe
your father's with you.

33:25.916 --> 33:27.135
I don't think
he trusts you anymore

33:27.179 --> 33:28.832
since you botched that job
last year

33:28.876 --> 33:31.139
and you lost your nerve.
- He trusts me.

33:31.183 --> 33:33.837
He's here.
We're in this together.

33:33.881 --> 33:36.144
- Prove it.
Put him on the phone.

33:36.188 --> 33:39.060
♪

33:39.104 --> 33:41.236
- The FBI wants to talk to you.

33:41.280 --> 33:48.243
♪

33:48.287 --> 33:50.506
- Blake Wilson?
- That's right.

33:50.550 --> 33:52.856
Who's this?
- Agent LaCroix.

33:52.900 --> 33:55.033
You know we have
Jeri Eaton in custody?

33:55.076 --> 33:56.382
- Yeah.

33:56.425 --> 33:58.949
- You curious to know
what's happening with her?

33:58.993 --> 34:01.343
- No.
- [scoffs]

34:01.387 --> 34:03.519
[whispering]
Passport.

34:03.563 --> 34:06.174
Well, thanks to Jeri,
we're all caught up

34:06.218 --> 34:08.611
on who's behind the body count.

34:08.655 --> 34:11.136
And killing the hostage--
that was Stevie's idea?

34:11.179 --> 34:12.659
- Yeah.

34:12.702 --> 34:16.010
- Now, you know I know there's
no way out of there alive

34:16.054 --> 34:18.621
unless you play this as smart
as I think you are.

34:18.665 --> 34:20.536
- Well aware of that.

34:20.580 --> 34:22.930
- Let me offer you a way out.

34:24.149 --> 34:25.106
- Okay.

34:27.108 --> 34:30.633
But you heard my son.
It's do or die.

34:32.157 --> 34:34.246
Just can't be any other way.

34:34.289 --> 34:40.643
♪

34:40.687 --> 34:42.558
- Let me come in and negotiate.

34:42.602 --> 34:44.212
- Okay.

34:44.256 --> 34:48.303
♪

34:48.347 --> 34:50.566
- Let's get wired up.

34:50.610 --> 34:52.220
- You sure?

34:52.264 --> 34:54.483
- Sounds like Stevie wantsto go out in a blaze of glory.

34:54.527 --> 34:56.137
Not Blake--I don't think

34:56.181 --> 34:58.052
he can shake his sonwithout some help.

34:58.096 --> 35:00.968
♪

35:01.011 --> 35:02.448
- It's done.

35:02.491 --> 35:04.363
- Thank you.

35:12.197 --> 35:14.851
- Hold your fire!
Agents going in!

35:14.895 --> 35:17.854
[dramatic music]

35:17.898 --> 35:21.249
♪

35:21.293 --> 35:22.859
- We want a car to the airport

35:22.903 --> 35:25.166
and a chopper
to anywhere we want.

35:25.210 --> 35:29.518
- I can't do that, but I'm
willing to meet you halfway.

35:29.562 --> 35:31.564
You release the hostages,

35:31.607 --> 35:33.653
and I'll secure an exit
for one of you.

35:33.696 --> 35:35.307
Which one of you,
you can decide.

35:35.350 --> 35:36.656
That's up to you guys.

35:36.699 --> 35:38.832
There's only one criminal
we want.

35:38.875 --> 35:40.834
- [screams]

35:40.877 --> 35:43.184
- You really think I'm just
gonna leave my dad behind?

35:43.228 --> 35:45.447
[tense music]

35:45.491 --> 35:48.537
- Stevie, look at me.

35:48.581 --> 35:49.886
Look at me, Stevie.

35:49.930 --> 35:52.193
♪

35:52.237 --> 35:55.501
I'm not afraid to go back.It's what I know.

35:55.544 --> 35:57.372
- No, there's got to be
another way.

35:57.416 --> 35:58.939
- There isn't.
You heard him.

35:58.982 --> 36:00.723
He's willing to do the time.

36:00.767 --> 36:02.682
♪

36:02.725 --> 36:04.336
- I robbed youof a real father,

36:04.379 --> 36:07.382
and I'm not gonnatake away your future, too.

36:07.426 --> 36:09.689
Just take the deal.
- I can't do that to you.

36:09.732 --> 36:12.213
- Damn it, Stevie!

36:12.257 --> 36:14.389
Why can't you just
do what I say for once?

36:14.433 --> 36:15.651
How in the hell
you think

36:15.695 --> 36:17.349
we got into this mess
in the first place?

36:17.392 --> 36:18.872
- Look, I know I screwed up,

36:18.915 --> 36:21.831
but from here on out,
I'm not letting you down, okay?

36:21.875 --> 36:23.398
No deal.

36:23.442 --> 36:29.535
♪

36:29.578 --> 36:32.494
- I'm offering you a way out.

36:32.538 --> 36:34.931
You're willing to die to save
your father from going to jail?

36:34.975 --> 36:38.848
- Damn right.
- You're a good kid, Stevie.

36:38.892 --> 36:41.634
Better than he deserves.

36:41.677 --> 36:43.549
Did he tell you
what he had planned?

36:44.941 --> 36:46.291
Did you tell him?

36:46.334 --> 36:53.341
♪

36:54.777 --> 36:56.388
- Jeri led us to the Albanians

36:56.431 --> 36:59.869
who were making passports
for your father.

36:59.913 --> 37:02.263
There's two passports here.

37:02.307 --> 37:03.786
♪

37:03.830 --> 37:05.440
One for Blake...

37:07.007 --> 37:09.009
And there's another one
here for--

37:09.052 --> 37:11.577
Well, you tell me.

37:11.620 --> 37:13.709
♪

37:13.753 --> 37:16.756
There's no passport
for you, Stevie.

37:16.799 --> 37:19.367
Jeri told us that Blake
was planning on killing you

37:19.411 --> 37:21.587
before he got to the border.

37:21.630 --> 37:24.764
- No, no,nobody was gonna kill you.

37:24.807 --> 37:27.288
No, the planwas to come back for you.

37:27.332 --> 37:33.686
♪

37:33.729 --> 37:34.991
Stevie.

37:35.035 --> 37:38.299
♪

37:38.343 --> 37:39.953
I-I...

37:39.996 --> 37:41.911
[suspenseful music]

37:41.955 --> 37:44.349
Whoa.
- Don't do it, Steven.

37:44.392 --> 37:47.308
Nobody needs to die here.
Just give me the gun.

37:47.352 --> 37:54.315
♪

37:54.359 --> 37:56.926
- Oh! God!

37:56.970 --> 37:59.451
You stupid--what'd you do that for?

37:59.494 --> 38:01.061
- You were really just gonna
get rid of me?

38:01.104 --> 38:04.717
- I should've walked awaywhen you came looking for me.

38:04.760 --> 38:07.372
This couldn't have worked outworse if I tried,

38:07.415 --> 38:10.766
you weak, pathetic...

38:11.854 --> 38:12.942
- Don't do it Steven.

38:12.986 --> 38:14.944
I know you want to,
and I know why.

38:14.988 --> 38:16.685
- I'm gonna go away
for the rest of my life

38:16.729 --> 38:17.991
no matter what, so why not?

38:18.034 --> 38:19.471
- Because then
I'll have to kill you,

38:19.514 --> 38:20.863
and I don't want to do that.

38:20.907 --> 38:22.343
Trust me, he's not worth it.

38:22.387 --> 38:29.350
♪

38:30.699 --> 38:32.745
- [sobs]

38:32.788 --> 38:35.487
I would've done anything
for him.

38:35.530 --> 38:39.099
- I know.
I hear you.

38:39.142 --> 38:43.016
All he does is take--
from you, from your mom.

38:43.059 --> 38:45.932
But you kill him,
he takes everything.

38:45.975 --> 38:48.021
♪

38:48.064 --> 38:50.806
You hear me, Steven?

38:50.850 --> 38:52.721
Steven, do you hear me?

38:52.765 --> 38:55.550
It's better for him to live
with what he's done.

38:55.594 --> 39:02.557
♪

39:13.176 --> 39:15.048
We're clear.

39:15.091 --> 39:17.529
- We're clear.
- We're clear!

39:17.572 --> 39:20.967
[handcuffs clicking]

39:21.010 --> 39:23.143
- Get up!

39:23.186 --> 39:27.408
- Well, you got me out alive.

39:27.452 --> 39:31.107
- Trust me, it wasn'tyour life I was trying to save.

39:31.151 --> 39:38.158
♪

39:39.202 --> 39:41.596
- Looks like Blake's
gonna pull through.

39:41.640 --> 39:43.685
- Somehow I'm not relieved.

39:45.208 --> 39:46.601
You know, the second time

39:46.645 --> 39:49.474
I went to the trackwith my dad, I wanted to go.

39:49.517 --> 39:52.955
I wanted to be like himwith his pals and his world.

39:52.999 --> 39:55.131
He started losing, as usual.

39:55.175 --> 39:57.612
Got drunk, as usual,

39:57.656 --> 40:00.615
and blamed mefor his bad luck.

40:00.659 --> 40:03.488
When I saw Stevie's picture,I thought to myself...

40:04.532 --> 40:05.881
"I know this kid."

40:07.535 --> 40:09.145
Five homicides later...

40:11.670 --> 40:13.628
- We all got blind spots, bro.

40:13.672 --> 40:16.544
You still got the job done.

40:20.635 --> 40:22.942
I'm heading up.
You coming?

40:22.985 --> 40:25.858
- No, I'm gonna sit for a bit.

40:33.605 --> 40:35.476
- I am donefor the night, Pete.

40:35.520 --> 40:37.478
You mind checkingon my to-go order?

40:37.522 --> 40:38.914
- Yeah, sure.

40:42.222 --> 40:44.224
- What'd you order?

40:44.267 --> 40:48.576
- The salmon.
- I was gonna order that.

40:48.620 --> 40:52.275
Any dessert?
- Tiramisu for my son.

40:54.190 --> 40:55.583
- How old?

40:55.627 --> 40:57.193
- 14 going on 40.

40:57.237 --> 40:59.674
Likes it with his decafcappuccino in the morning.

40:59.718 --> 41:01.154
- [laughs]

41:01.197 --> 41:04.157
- I'm usually up and outby the time he gets up, so...

41:04.200 --> 41:05.767
- Restaurant opens that early?

41:05.811 --> 41:09.205
- No, I teachspecial education.

41:09.249 --> 41:10.859
- Really?

41:12.165 --> 41:15.037
Well...

41:15.081 --> 41:17.213
that's important work.

41:19.912 --> 41:21.217
- And what do you do?

41:23.785 --> 41:25.874
- [chuckles]

41:25.918 --> 41:28.007
Um...

41:28.050 --> 41:30.792
I'm in law enforcement.

41:30.836 --> 41:33.055
- Hmm.

41:33.099 --> 41:35.188
Wouldn't have taken you
for a cop.

41:35.231 --> 41:37.016
- What would you take me for?

41:37.059 --> 41:40.628
- I don't know.
A philosophy professor.

41:40.672 --> 41:43.196
- [laughs]
Maybe in another life.

41:43.239 --> 41:44.893
- Here you go.
- [chuckles]

41:44.937 --> 41:46.808
Thanks, Pete.

41:47.896 --> 41:49.071
- Have a good night.

41:49.115 --> 41:52.292
[soft music]

41:52.335 --> 41:54.033
♪

41:54.076 --> 41:56.818
- Lovely talkingwith you, Professor...

41:56.862 --> 41:58.559
- Jess.

41:58.603 --> 42:01.040
♪

42:01.083 --> 42:02.084
- Leslie.

42:04.304 --> 42:05.871
Have a good rest of your night.

42:05.914 --> 42:07.307
- You too.

42:07.350 --> 42:13.574
♪

43:00.752 --> 43:01.230
[wolf howls]
